Homepage: https://metacpan.org/release/Gnome2-GConf
Description: Perl interface to the GNOME GConf library
 This module is part of Gtk2-Perl. Gnome2::GConf allows a Perl developer to use
 the GConf configuration system to store/retrieve the configuration of an
 application.
 .
 The GConf system is a powerful configuration manager based on a user daemon
 that handles a set of key and value pairs, and notifies any changes of the
 value to every program that monitors those keys. GConf is used by GNOME 2.x.
 .
 The Perl bindings follow the C API very closely, and the C reference
 documentation should be considered the canonical source:
 http://developer.gnome.org/doc/API/2.0/gconf/index.html
 .
 To discuss gtk2-perl, ask questions and flame/praise the authors,
 join gtk-perl-list at https://lists.gnome.org
